      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHERESWALLY (10) showed good promise as a juvenile, winning his first three starts including a Breeders Challenge heat before drawing wide when seventh in a semi final of that series at Menangle when last seen in October. Likely to have developed with maturity and has been readied with two trial placings. SEASIDE SID (9) returns from a spell of four-and-a-half months having ended his juvenile season with a win by 3.6 metres at this circuit and distance. Readied with two trials, easily winning the latest, and draws to enjoy a pretty soft run so could open this campaign with a win. CAPTURE OUR HEART NZ (8) raced just once last campaign when down the track in a Breeders Crown heat but ended the previous preparation with a win here and while drawn wide she was readied for her return with a trial win. LOOKMEOVER NZ (6) was a big improver when beaten 2.2m into second last week at Bathurst and could progress further third-up.",
